requires.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782804880814,"responseId":"gen-1782804881-8Cr75Vz0ABbSmN74KeHb","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed the complete arbitration record. Let me analyze the key evidence:\n\n**Proposition**: Between market creation on April 20, 2026, and December 31, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, Clavicular made a credible announcement that he and a partner were expecting a baby through pregnancy.\n\n**Standard**: Preponderance of the evidence.\n\n**Key Record Evidence:**\n\n1. **Official Market Rule** (PX-1, DX-1, PX-4): Requires \"credible announcements\" from Clavicular or representatives, or \"definitive consensus of credible media reporting.\" Jokes don't qualify.\n\n2. **Final Market Resolution**: Yes outcome after two dispute cycles (outcomePrices [1,0]).\n\n3. **Forbes** (PX-3): Describes dispute as being about \"a streamer who told his audience he had gotten a girl pregnant\" - favorable characterization. But also notes market description/platform clarification said No while price said Yes.\n\n4. **Times of India fact-check** (PX-5): Explicitly states \"No video confirms a pregnancy. No statement from Clavicular confirms it either.\" Says the viral claim is \"false and likely came from a mix of jokes, clips taken out of context.\"\n\n5. **Hindustan Times/Express Tribune** (PX-3): Frame remarks as a \"pregnancy contest\" proposal with quotes like \"I must have children\" and \"I will be a dad in the next few months\" - future-oriented, not an existing pregnancy announcement.\n\n6. **Record Gaps** (PX-6): No original VOD/transcript, no Polymarket clarification, no UMA records, no primary Clavicular statement preserved.\n\n**Analysis:**\n\nThe record shows conflicting secondary reporting. Forbes provides one favorable characterization, but TOI, Hindustan Times, and Express Tribune all describe the preserved quotes as future-oriented contest/stunt language, not an announcement of an existing pregnancy. The official Yes resolution is circumstantial but does not reveal what evidence the resolver relied on - and the record explicitly states Forbes reported the platform clarification pointed No.\n\nThere is no \"definitive consensus of credible media\" - the media reports conflict. There is no preserved primary statement from Clavicular announcing an existing partner pregnancy. The preserved quotes are about wanting children in the future, not expecting a baby now.\n\nUnder preponderance, the evidence does not show a qualifying announcement is more likely than not. The defense's explanation (rumor cycle, contest proposal, future vows, debunked viral claims) fits the admitted record at least as well as plaintiff's theory.\n\nI will vote **not_demonstrated**.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c66338bc73d545f4b8e61950","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record contains conflicting secondary reports and no preserved primary statement from Clavicular announcing an existing partner pregnancy. The preserved quotes describe future-oriented contest/stunt language, and Times of India explicitly states no statement from Clavicular confirmed a pregnancy. The final Yes resolution does not establish what evidence the resolver relied upon, and there is no definitive consensus of credible media as the rule requires.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The admitted record contains conflicting secondary reports and no preserved primary statement from Clavicular announcing an existing partner pregnancy. The preserved quotes describe future-oriented contest/stunt language, and Times of India explicitly states no statement from Clavicular confirmed a pregnancy. The final Yes resolution does not establish what evidence the resolver relied upon, and there is no definitive consensus of credible media as the rule requires.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782804880814,"responseId":"gen-1782804881-8Cr75Vz0ABbSmN74KeHb","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}}
